14. Create Basic Data Visualization and Dashboard Creation using Tableau
✅ Step 1 — Connect Excel to Tableau
1.	Open Tableau Desktop
2.	Click Microsoft Excel
3.	Select Tableau_Lab_SalesData.xlsx
4.	Drag SalesData sheet to the canvas
5.	Click Sheet 1
You will see fields:
Order ID, Order Date, Region, Category, Sub-Category, Sales, Profit
________________________________________
📊 Step 2 — Bar Chart (Sales by Region)
1.	Drag Region → Rows
2.	Drag Sales → Columns
3.	Chart becomes Bar chart
4.	Click Sort Descending
5.	Rename sheet: Sales by Region
________________________________________
📈 Step 3 — Line Chart (Sales over Time)
1.	New Sheet
2.	Drag Order Date → Columns
3.	Change it to Month
4.	Drag Sales → Rows
5.	Change Marks to Line
6.	Rename sheet: Monthly Sales Trend
________________________________________
🥧 Step 4 — Pie Chart (Sales by Category)
1.	New Sheet
2.	Change Marks → Pie
3.	Drag Category → Color
4.	Drag Sales → Angle
5.	Drag Sales → Label
6.	Rename sheet: Category Wise Sales
________________________________________

🎯 Aim
To connect an Excel dataset to Tableau and create different visualizations (Bar chart, Line chart, Pie chart, Map) and combine them into an interactive dashboard using filters.
________________________________________
🧭 Algorithm (12 Steps)
1.	Start the Tableau Desktop application.
2.	Select Microsoft Excel from the Connect panel.
3.	Browse and choose the file Tableau_Lab_SalesData.xlsx.
4.	Load the Excel file into Tableau by opening the data source page.
5.	Drag the SalesData worksheet to the data canvas.
6.	Verify that all fields are loaded correctly in the Data pane.
7.	Click on Sheet 1 to begin visualization.
8.	Drag the Region dimension to the Rows shelf.
9.	Drag the Sales measure to the Columns shelf.
10.	Observe the automatically generated bar chart.
11.	Sort the bar chart in descending order based on sales values.
12.	Rename the worksheet as Sales by Region.

